{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Electric}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/GO|species=Blitzle}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Electric|prevnum=521|prev=Unfezant|nextnum=523|next=Zebstrika|roundleft=bl|roundright=br}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Blitzle\n|jname=シママ\n|tmname=Shimama\n|category=Electrified\n|typebox=1\n|type1=Electric\n|abilityn=d\n|ability1=Lightning Rod\n|ability2=Motor Drive\n|abilityd=Sap Sipper\n|ndex=522\n|udex=028\n|u2dex=147\n|height-ftin=2\'07"\n|height-m=0.8\n|weight-lbs=65.7\n|weight-kg=29.8\n|egggroupn=1\n|egggroup1=Field\n|eggcycles=20\n|expyield=59\n|lv100exp=1,000,000\n|gendercode=127\n|color=Black\n|catchrate=190\n|body=08\n|evtotal=1\n|evsp=1\n|pokefordex=blitzle\n|generation=5\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Blitzle\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'シママ\'\'\' \'\'Shimama\'\') is an {{type|Electric}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation V]].\n\nIt [[Evolution|evolves]] into {{p|Zebstrika}} starting at [[level]] 27.\n\n==Biology==\nBlitzle is a black, zebra-like Pokémon with thick, double-pointed white stripes on its neck, chest, back, and hind legs. It has a rounded muzzle with a large, dark nose and oval, blue eyes with yellow sclerae. On top of its head are short, triangular ears with blue insides. Below the knees, its legs are white with black hooves. Its tail is stubby, white, and has two points. Running up its neck is a spiky, white mane, which culminates at the front in a long extension that resembles a lightning bolt. This mane captures and stores electricity, which flashes whenever this Pokémon discharges energy. It communicates with other members of its species by controlling the rhythm and frequency of these flashes. During lightning storms, Blitzle ventures out to recharge its mane with lightning bolts.\n\n==In the anime==\n[[File:Stephan Blitzle.png|250px|left|thumb|Blitzle in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n===Major appearances===\nBlitzle debuted in \'\'[[BW028|Oshawott\'s Lost Scalchop!]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Stephan]]. It was used in a {{pkmn|battle}} against {{Ash}}, where it went up against {{AP|Oshawott}} and caused him to lose his [[Scalchop and seamitar|scalchop]]. They later had a [[rematch]], where it was defeated. Blitzle was revealed to have evolved into Zebstrika before \'\'[[BW039|Reunion Battles In Nimbasa!]]\'\'.\n\nA Blitzle appeared in [[M14|\'\'White—Victini and Zekrom\'\' and \'\'Black—Victini and Reshiram\'\']], under the ownership of [[Luisa]]. In the former movie, it was rescued in the middle of the desert by [[Damon]] when it injured its leg, and it was returned to Luisa with the help of Damon\'s {{p|Reuniclus}}\'s {{m|Psychic}}. In the latter movie, it made a brief cameo appearance while fulfilling a similar role.\n\n===Minor appearances===\nThree Blitzle appeared in \'\'[[BW034|Gotta Catch A Roggenrola!]]\'\'.\n\nMultiple Blitzle appeared in \'\'[[BW051|Lost at the Stamp Rally!]]\'\'.\n\nMultiple Blitzle appeared in \'\'[[BW053|A Maractus Musical!]]\'\', including one in a flashback.\n\nMultiple Blitzle appeared in \'\'[[BW056|The Lonely Deino!]]\'\', under the care of a {{pkmn|Day Care}} owner named [[Bobby]].\n\nA Blitzle appeared in \'\'[[BW057|The Mighty Accelguard to the Rescue!]]\'\', under the ownership of a shopper at the {{DL|Driftveil City|Market|Driftveil Market}}.\n\nMultiple Blitzle appeared in \'\'[[BW059|Stopping the Rage of Legends! Part 1]]\'\'.\n\nA Blitzle appeared in \'\'[[BW065|Battling the Bully!]]\'\'. It was a Pokémon owned by [[Sean]]\'s father, which he loaned to his son and [[Glenn]] to use in a practice battle.\n\nA {{pkmn|Trainer}}\'s Blitzle made a cameo appearance in \'\'[[BW067|Cilan Takes Flight]]\'\'.\n\nTwo Blitzle made a cameo appearance in \'\'[[BW069|Climbing the Tower of Success!]]\'\', both under the ownership of a Trainer.\n\nA Blitzle briefly appeared in \'\'[[BW071|Search for the Clubultimate!]]\'\'.\n\nA Blitzle briefly appeared in \'\'[[BW080|Clash of the Connoisseurs!]]\'\', where it was one of the Pokémon [[Burgundy]], disguised as Fauxgundy, reviewed as a possible Pokémon for [[Marigold]].\n\nA Blitzle made a cameo appearance in \'\'[[BW081|Crisis at the Ferroseed Research!]]\'\'.\n\nA Blitzle made a cameo appearance in \'\'[[BW083|Rocking at the Virbank Gym! Part 1]]\'\'.\n\nMultiple Blitzle made cameo appearances in \'\'[[BW085|All for the Love of Meloetta!]]\'\'.\n\nMultiple Blitzle appeared in \'\'[[M15|Kyurem VS. The Sword of Justice]]\'\' during the {{OBP|Swords of Justice|M15}} legend.\n\nA Trainer\'s Blitzle appeared in \'\'[[BW090|Jostling for the Junior Cup!]]\'\'.\n\nMultiple Blitzle appeared in \'\'[[BW102|Team Eevee and the Pokémon Rescue Squad!]]\'\', where they were among the residents of a ranch at [[Virgil]]\'s house.\n\nTwo Blitzle appeared in \'\'[[BW103|Curtain Up, Unova League!]]\'\', both under the ownership of a Trainer.\n\nA Trainer\'s Blitzle appeared in \'\'[[BW104|Mission: Defeat Your Rival!]]\'\'.\n\nTwo Blitzle appeared in a flashback in \'\'[[BW112|Team Plasma\'s Pokémon Power Plot!]]\'\'.\n\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Animedexheader|Unova}}\n{{Animedexbody|BW028|Blitzle|Ash\'s Pokédex|Blitzle, the Electrified Pokémon. Blitzle catches electricity and stores it in its mane, which glows when the electricity is discharged.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Best Wishes\'\'|Unova}}\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Andy Blitzle Adventures.png|100px|thumb|Blitzle in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n===In the Pocket Monsters BW: The Heroes of Fire and Thunder manga===\nA Blitzle appeared in \'\'[[FAT2|The King\'s Identity...!!]]\'\'.\n\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\nA {{tc|Hiker}} named Andy uses a Blitzle during his [[Triple Battle]] with {{adv|Black}} in \'\'[[PS464|Black\'s First Trainer Battle]]\'\'. However, he was defeated after Andy became dehydrated.\n\nA Trainer\'s Blitzle appeared in \'\'[[PS466|An Odd Speech]]\'\' and \'\'[[PS486|Unraveling Mysteries]]\'\'.\n\nA Blitzle appeared in \'\'[[PS471|Battle at the Dreamyard]]\'\'.\n\n[[Elesa]] has a {{p|Zebstrika}} that she has owned since she was young and it was a Blitzle. It appeared in a flashback in \'\'[[PS484|Battle on a Roller Coaster]]\'\'.\n\n===In the Pokémon Pocket Monsters manga===\nA Blitzle appeared in [[PMHGSS23]].\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Blitzle (TCG)}}\n\n==Game data==\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Dex/Header|type=Electric}}\n{{Dex/NA|gen=V}}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=V|reg1=Unova|num1=028|label1={{gameabbrev5|BW}}:|reg2=Unova|num2=147|label2={{gameabbrev5|B2W2}}:}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Black|t=FFF|entry=Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use their flashing manes to communicate with one another.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=White|entry=When thunderclouds cover the sky, it will appear. It can catch lightning with its mane and store the electricity.}}\n{{Dex/Entry2|v=Black 2|v2=White 2|t=FFF|entry=Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use the frequency and rhythm of these flashes to communicate.}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=VI|reg1=Kalos|reg2=Hoenn}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=X|t=FFF|entry=When thunderclouds cover the sky, it will appear. It can catch lightning with its mane and store the electricity.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Y|entry=Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use the frequency and rhythm of these flashes to communicate.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Omega Ruby|t=FFF|entry=When thunderclouds cover the sky, it will appear. It can catch lightning with its mane and store the electricity.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Alpha Sapphire|t=FFF|entry=Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use the frequency and rhythm of these flashes to communicate.}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=VII|reg1=Alola|reg2=Kanto}}\n{{Dex/NE|[[Generation VII]]}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Footer}}\n\n===Game locations===\n{{Availability/Header|type=Electric}}\n{{Availability/NA|gen=V}}\n{{Availability/Gen|gen=V}}\n{{Availability/Entry2|v=Black|v2=White|t=FFF|area={{rt|3|Unova}}}}\n{{Availability/Entry2|v=Black 